<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,994,1484]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,317,1110,1136]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This species is distinct from any other one from the Apennines by frontal impressions of head relatively deep, basal impressions of pronotum foveate (not linear), elytral striae irregularly but finely punctate, each elytron usually with 
<number box="[590,605,1188,1214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="4.0">4</number>
dorsal SP and situation of second dorsal SP in middle of interval 
<number box="[1421,1436,1188,1214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
(equidistantly from striae 
<number box="[459,474,1226,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number box="[533,549,1226,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="3.0">3</number>
), medial lobe of aedeagus laterally curved, with twin-peaked apex sharply bent downwards and lobes twisted ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[690,772,1265,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 - 6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1245,1269]" captionTargetBox="[174,1404,191,1244]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,157,1276]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 - 6. Median lobe of aedeagus left lateral view and parameres of Italian Platyderus: Fig. 1. Platyderus casalei sp. n., holotype; Fig. 2. P. magrinii Degiovanni, “ Mte Graeco ”; Fig. 3. P. neapolitanus Chaudoir, “ Emery Napels ”; Fig. 4. P. paganettii sp. n., holotype; Fig. 5. P. vignai sp. n., holotype; Fig. 6. P. vignai sp. n., holotype, parameres." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190889/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
Figs. 
<number box="[757,772,1265,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="1.7">1</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[787,804,1265,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 - 10" captionStartId="3.[151,276,1325,1349]" captionTargetBox="[186,1406,599,1276]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,569,1316]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 - 10. Median lobe of aedeagus right lateral view and copulatory piece of Italian Platyderus: Fig. 7. Platyderus casalei sp. n., holotype; Fig. 8. P. paganettii sp. n., holotype; Fig. 9. P. vignai sp. n., holotype; Fig. 10. P. paganettii sp. n., holotype, dorsal and ventral shape of copulatory piece." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190890/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[818,848,1265,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 - 18" captionStartId="6.[151,270,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[204,1415,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,194,1847]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11 - 18. Median lobe of aedeagus, ventral and dorsal views of Italian Platyderus: Fig. 11. Platyderus casalei sp. n., holotype, ventral view; Fig. 12. P. magrinii Degiovanni, “ Mte Graeco ”, ventral view; Fig. 13. P. neapolitanus Chaudoir, “ Emery Napels ”, ventral view; Fig. 14. P. paganettii sp. n., holotype, ventral view; Fig. 15. P. vignai sp. n., holotype, ventral view; Fig. 16. Platyderus casalei sp. n., holotype, dorsal view; Fig. 17. P. neapolitanus Chaudoir, “ Emery Napels ”, dorsal view; Fig. 18. P. vignai sp. n., holotype, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190891/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<number box="[818,848,1265,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
), copulatory piece with prominent medial lobe in front (
<figureCitation box="[224,310,1304,1330]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 - 18" captionStartId="6.[151,270,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[204,1415,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,194,1847]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11 - 18. Median lobe of aedeagus, ventral and dorsal views of Italian Platyderus: Fig. 11. Platyderus casalei sp. n., holotype, ventral view; Fig. 12. P. magrinii Degiovanni, “ Mte Graeco ”, ventral view; Fig. 13. P. neapolitanus Chaudoir, “ Emery Napels ”, ventral view; Fig. 14. P. paganettii sp. n., holotype, ventral view; Fig. 15. P. vignai sp. n., holotype, ventral view; Fig. 16. Platyderus casalei sp. n., holotype, dorsal view; Fig. 17. P. neapolitanus Chaudoir, “ Emery Napels ”, dorsal view; Fig. 18. P. vignai sp. n., holotype, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190891/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[279,310,1304,1330]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName box="[475,588,1304,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="casalei" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[475,490,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[505,588,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">casalei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[596,662,1303,1329]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[596,662,1303,1329]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is distinct from 
<taxonomicName box="[855,1004,1304,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paganettii" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[855,870,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[885,1004,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">paganettii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1012,1078,1303,1329]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1012,1078,1303,1329]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the non-overlapping values of the ratios PW/HW, PW/PL, and EW/PW.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" type="description">
