<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="44" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,526]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,306,332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Etymology</emphasis>
. Dedicated to Prof. Dr. Achille Casale for his important contributions to the systematics and taxonomy of the Italian and European 
<taxonomicName box="[601,724,345,371]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carabidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,526]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,267,383,409]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Notes</emphasis>
. The significant differences in the external structure of the male genitalia between 
<taxonomicName box="[1248,1361,384,410]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="casalei" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1248,1262,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1278,1361,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">casalei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1369,1436,383,409]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1369,1436,383,409]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[200,349,422,448]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paganettii" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[200,215,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[230,349,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">paganettii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[356,422,422,448]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[356,422,422,448]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, as well the state of several external special features (foveae of head; basal impression of pronotum) and non-overlapping ratios (PW/HW, PW/PL, EW/PW) could be the effect of rapid sympatric isolation of these related taxa.
</paragraph>
